So, there's a question from, sorry if I mispronounce your name, Jerry Palak.

00:40:49.000 --> 00:40:53.000
Does it work as CPU or NGPU parallel computing?

00:40:53.000 --> 00:40:57.000
This is a CPU specific solution.

00:40:57.000 --> 00:40:59.000
It's not GPU aware.

00:40:59.000 --> 00:41:03.000
So, the goal here is to make the best use of your CPU.

00:41:03.000 --> 00:41:08.000
There are packages for computation on the GPU,

00:41:08.000 --> 00:41:12.000
but Rcpparallel is specifically targeting the processor.

00:41:12.000 --> 00:41:16.000
If you're writing code to run on other computers,

00:41:16.000 --> 00:41:20.000
is there a way to determine the number of cores available on that machine from within R?

00:41:20.000 --> 00:41:23.000
And I believe that's true.

00:41:23.000 --> 00:41:26.000
I might not get it right on the first try,

00:41:26.000 --> 00:41:32.000
but let's see if it's in the dot machine or dot platform.

