So, here at the github.io Rcpparallel,

00:41:53.000 --> 00:41:59.000
this is where all the information about some of the nitty-gritty stuff in Rcpparallel can be answered.

00:41:59.000 --> 00:42:05.000
Can I define my own ranges for splitting up data across the workers?

00:42:05.000 --> 00:42:12.000
So, you can tweak the parameters that TBB uses to divide the data into separate ranges,

00:42:12.000 --> 00:42:18.000
but I don't think you can take the actual level of granularity to say,

00:42:18.000 --> 00:42:21.000
oh, I want this worker to specifically have...

00:42:21.000 --> 00:42:23.000
Well, you can tweak the grain size.

00:42:23.000 --> 00:42:29.000
So, you can say, oh, I want, say, 256 or 512 bytes per worker or maybe probably more than that,

00:42:29.000 --> 00:42:35.000
but I believe tweaking the grain size allows you to effectively define the size of ranges,

00:42:35.000 --> 00:42:41.000
although I don't think you could say you could customize different sizes for different workers.

